not modify. Summarize: existing stages, likely missing builder/QA task coverage, and suggested watched subtask scopes.\n\n**Actual Need**: Engineering leader needs a concise health check on this multi-agent novel writing workflow project — what's covered, what's likely missing, and what subtasks should be watched in a task-hall style system.\n\n**Success Looks Like**: A concise summary with: (1) existing stage coverage, (2) likely gaps (builder/QA tasks), (3) recommended watched subtask scopes.\n</analysis>\n\n<results>\n<files>\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\workflow\\design.md - 1039-line master design doc; defines 8 stages (A–H), 14 agent roles, 10 canon asset types, parallel/serial rules, review dimensions, failure modes, and skill-library落地建议\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\workflow\\top-agent.md - 52-line top-agent prompt; defines 8 stage gates, task-hall watched task protocol, and task-link completion logic\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\workflow\\runbook.md - 46-line runbook; project bootstrap, parallel task publishing, gate review logic, chapter write order\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\example-project\\ - skeleton with canon/, chapter-briefs/, drafts/, polished/, repair/, review/\n- D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\templates\\ - reusable templates for new projects\n</files>\n\n<answer>\n\n## xuanhuan-novel-workflow: Summary for Engineering Leader\n\n### Existing Stages (A–H, fully defined)\n\n| Stage | Name | Key Output | Gate? |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| A | 立项与读者承诺 | story-brief, reader-appeal, style-guide | Yes |\n| B | 世界与规则底盘 | world-bible, power-system, factions, glossary | Yes (Gate 1) |\n| C | 人物系统 | cast-ledger, relationship-map, character-arcs | Yes (Gate 2) |\n| D | 主线与分卷规划 | master-outline, volume-plan, foreshadow-log | Yes (Gate 3) |\n| E | 章节拆解 | chapter-briefs + checklists | Yes (Gate 4) |\n| F | 正文草稿 | drafts/chapters/ | No (but gated by E) |\n| G | 质量复审与返工 | continuity/appeal/style reviews + repair plan | Yes (conditional) |\n| H | canon 资产更新 | Updated cast-ledger, timeline, foreshadow-log, continuity-log | Yes |\n\n### Likely Missing Builder/QA Task Coverage\n\n1. **Builder tasks — implicit but not surfaced as watched subtasks:**\n   - `power-system` and `factions` generation in Stage B are treated as single agents, not parallelizable sub-tasks (e.g., realms hierarchy, resource types, faction economics should be separable).\n   - `cast-ledger` and `relationship-map` in Stage C are merged; a large cast needs parallel character-pool tasks (protagonist, antagonists, supporting pool, namedNPC pool).\n   - `foreshadow-log` maintenance is a recurring subtask not shown in task-hall terms — each chapter generates delta that needs a watched subtask to track.\n   - `terminology-glossary` updates are untracked; name collisions proliferate in long-running serials.\n\n2. **QA tasks — present in design but underspecified as watched subtasks:**\n   - Stage G lists three review types (continuity, appeal, style) but publishes no watched subtasks for them; only the final repair plan is implicit.\n   - `timeline.md` maintenance has no dedicated QA watcher — timeline drift is a top failure mode in the design itself.\n   - `战力/continuity check` is high-severity but not isolated as a repeatable watched QA subtask between chapters.\n   -返工 (rework) loop lacks a `rework-review` watcher to confirm fixes closed the issue without regressing other canon.\n\n3. **Executor/Builder coordination gap:**\n   - The design mentions `task-hall publish-raw --publish-mode watched` but only 5 parallel tasks are listed in the runbook; the full 10+ task types from the design (Section 11) are not surfaced in the runbook as executable watched tasks.\n\n### Suggested Watched Subtask Scopes\n\n**Pre-write (Stages A–D) — publish in parallel:**\n1. `xuanhuan-genre-brief` — story-brief + reader-appeal\n2. `xuanhuan-worldbuilding` — world-bible + glossary (parallel: geography draft, history draft, faction draft)\n3. `xuanhuan-power-system` — power-system + resource/cost matrix\n4. `xuanhuan-cast-design` — cast-ledger + relationship-map (parallel: protagonist card, antagonist pool, supporting pool)\n5. `xuanhuan-outline-planner` — master-outline + volume-plan + foreshadow-log seed\n\n**Per-chapter (Stages E–H) — recurring watched tasks:**\n6. `xuanhuan-chapter-brief` — one per chapter, gated by D output\n7. `xuanhuan-draft-writer` — one per chapter, gated by brief\n8. `xuanhuan-continuity-review` — standalone QA watcher; outputs issue list\n9. `xuanhuan-appeal-review` — standalone QA watcher; outputs issue list\n10. `xuanhuan-style-review` — standalone QA watcher; outputs issue list\n11. `xuanhuan-repair-merge` — consolidates 8+9+10 into repair plan; not parallel\n12. `xuanhuan-revision` — rework agent, gated by repair plan\n13. `xuanhuan-canon-delta` — canon updater; updates cast/timeline/foreshadow/continuity-log\n14. `xuanhuan-timeline-watch` — recurring QA watcher (not in current docs); flags timeline drift between chapters\n\n**Critical gap to add:** A `xuanhuan-timeline-watch` watched task after every Stage H to catch timeline inconsistencies before the next chapter brief is issued.\n\n</answer>\n\n<next_steps>\n- Add `timeline-watch` and `foreshadow-state-check` as recurring QA watched subtasks in runbook.md and top-agent.md\n- Surface all 10+ task-hall task types from design §11 explicitly in runbook instead of the current 5\n- Consider separating `power-system` and `foreshadow-log` into parallel sub-tasks for large casts (100+ chapters) where single-agent bottlenecks will appear\n- No file modifications were made per instruction\n</next_steps>","metadata":{"truncated":false,"task_id":"bg_83e82c4f","agent":"explore","category":"","description":"Inspect workflow assets","sessionId":"ses_23302e995ffeoj0cO9AcujvbbW"},"title":"explore - Inspect workflow assets","time":{"start":