{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777260704589,"sessionID":"ses_233033afeffe9G1blGyyhhKVWG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"background_output","callID":"call_FoA9Bgt6efuCH7CqD6heeZK1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"block":false,"full_session":false,"include_thinking":false,"include_tool_results":false,"message_limit":20,"since_message_id":"","task_id":"bg_a93423f4","thinking_max_chars":2000,"timeout":60000},"output":"Task Result\n\nTask ID: bg_a93423f4\nDescription: Inspect task-hall patterns\nDuration: 1m 0s\nSession ID: ses_23302e89affe6y8N0okemqUGy8\n\n---\n\nThe user wants me to investigate task-hall/task-link usage patterns and existing tasks related to \"xuanhuan\" or \"workflow\" under the specified path. They want to understand how to publish/link/report safely and identify any prior related task IDs/artifacts to avoid duplication.\n\nLet me start by exploring the directory structure they mentioned:\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\tasks`\n\nI should also look at task-hall and task-link more broadly to understand the patterns.\n\nLet me launch multiple parallel searches to understand the structure and find relevant content.\n\n\n<analysis>\n**Literal Request**: Inspect task-hall/task-link usage patterns and existing tasks related to \"xuanhuan\" or \"workflow\" under `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\tasks`\n\n**Actual Need**: Understand how to safely publish/link/report tasks, identify prior related task IDs or artifacts to avoid duplicating work, and learn the established patterns for task management in this workspace.\n\n**Success Looks Like**: A clear summary of the task publishing/linking/reporting workflow, plus a list of any existing xuanhuan or workflow-related task IDs/paths to avoid duplicating.\n</analysis>\n\nI'll launch parallel searches to explore the task-hall structure and find xuanhuan/workflow-related content.\n\n\nThe grep tool failed because `rg` (ripgrep) isn't available. Let me use the glob tool to find files first, then read them.\n\n\nLet me use glob and read to explore the task-hall structure instead.\n\n\nThe glob is not finding files - maybe the issue is with the path format. Let me try different approaches - using read for directories and looking for specific files.\n\n\nNow let me explore the state/tasks directory and task-links directory to find any existing tasks related to xuanhuan or workflow.\n\n\nNow let me explore the tasks directory and task-links to find any existing tasks related to xuanhuan or workflow.\n\n\nNow I have a very clear picture. Let me also look at the task-link subcommand documentation in the README and the `task-link` command in cli.package.json, and maybe look at the actual task-link JSON files to understand the structure. Let me also look at one or two xuanhuan task directories to see the actual task.md and artifacts.\n\nLet me also read the task-link files in the task-links directory and maybe look at a couple of the actual task directories to see what's inside them.\n\n\nLet me also inspect the actual task-link JSON files and a couple of xuanhuan-related task directories to see the full artifact picture.\n\n\nNow I have a thorough picture of the task-hall and task-link systems. Let me summarize the findings comprehensively.\n\n\n<results>\n\n<files>\n\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\README.md` — full protocol documentation for task-hall including publish/link/report lifecycle\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\cli.package.json` — command registry; `task-link` subcommands: `report`, `complete`, `continue`, `switch-agent`, `show`\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\listings.json` — current task index with status, tags, priority, publisher metadata\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\task-links\\` — per-task JSON files tracking `watched` publisher-builder lifecycle\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\monitor\\lifecycle-state.json` — aggregated lifecycle state; 4 active task-links, 0 pending callbacks\n- `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\task-hall\\state\\tasks\\` — 24 task directories; each has `meta.json`, `task.md`, `claims.jsonl`, `submissions.jsonl`\n\n</files>\n\n<answer>\n\n## task-hall / task-link Usage Patterns\n\n### Three ways to publish a task\n\n| Method | Command | Frontdesk review? |\n|--------|---------|-------------------|\n| **Recommended** — JSON request | `mycli task-hall submit-request <path-to-request.json>` | Yes, auto-generates `task.md` with `## 领取门槛` |\n| Direct markdown upload | `mycli task-hall upload <task.md> [kind] [priority] [tags] [title]` | No |\n| Upload + publish | `mycli task-hall upload-publish <task.md> ...` | No |\n| Raw publish (advanced) | `mycli task-hall publish-raw <task.md>` | No |\n\n### task-link lifecycle (publisher-builder pattern)\n\ntask-link is a **watched publisher-builder protocol** separate from the standard claim/submit flow. A task with `publish_mode: \"watched\"` enters task-link tracking when created:\n\n1. **Publisher** creates/owns the task; task status remains `listed` or `claimed` while `current_agent` executes.\n2. **Executor** (`current_agent`) runs the work and calls `mycli task-hall task-link report <task-id> <report.md>` — this writes a `task-link-report-*.md` and creates a `callback` entry.\n3. **Callbacks** are dispatched to the `publisher_agent` via `mycli task-hall dispatch-callbacks`. Dispatched callbacks go to `callback-queue/` with `.output.txt` results.\n4. **Publisher** reviews and calls `mycli task-hall task-link complete <task-id>` (closes the link) or `continue` / `switch-agent`.\n\nOther task-link subcommands:\n- `mycli task-hall task-link show <task-id>` — display link status\n- `mycli task-hall task-link switch-agent <task-id> <new-agent>` — reassign executor\n\n### Status model\n\n```\ndraft → listed → claimed → done\n                  ↘ cancelled\n                  ↘ archived\n```\n\n### Report submission (standard claim path)\n\n```\nmycli task-hall review-submission <task-id> <task-report.md>\n```\nCalls `opencode/task-hall-reviewer` agent. Four reviewer conclusions: `complete`, `return_to_agent`, `relist_as_is`, `revise_and_relist`.\n\n---\n\n## Prior Xuanhuan / Workflow Related Task IDs (avoid duplication)\n\n| Task ID | Title | Status | Tags |\n|--------|-------|--------|------|\n| `task_20260425_020706_ca7376` | 设计玄幻小说写作 agent 工作流 | **done** | `writing`, `workflow`, `agent`, `xuanhuan`, `novel` |\n| `task_20260427_010906_857c20` | 工程部 Leader 接手玄幻小说工作流项目 | **claimed** (active) | `engineering xuanhuan leader` |\n| `task_20260427_011633_f950d3` | 玄幻小说写作工作流搭建任务（二次发布） | **listed** (open) | `engineering xuanhuan workflow` |\n| `task_20260427_012215_9f6a87` | 玄幻工作流验证：世界观与升级体系实跑 | **done** | `xuanhuan validation worldbuilding` |\n| `task_20260427_012215_2911de` | 玄幻工作流验证：章节 brief 与正文草稿实跑 | **done** | `xuanhuan validation chapter` |\n| `task_20260427_012216_cc0b60` | 玄幻工作流验证：审校与返工流程检查 | **done** | `xuanhuan validation review` |\n| `task_20260427_012216_f3be94` | 玄幻工作流验证：整体架构 QA 与一致性检查 | **done** | `xuanhuan validation qa` |\n\n### Key artifact paths to know (do not duplicate)\n\n- **Workflow project root**: `D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\` (referenced in QA validation results)\n- **Example project**: `D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\example-project\\` containing `review/`, `repair/`, `brief/`, `draft/` subdirs\n- **Workflow architecture QA report**: `example-project/review/workflow-architecture-qa.md`\n- **World-building canon artifacts**: `world-bible/`, `power-system/`, `factions/`, `terminology-glossary/`, `cast-ledger/`\n\n### Active (non-done) xuanhuan/workflow tasks to check before publishing\n\n| Task ID | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| `task_20260427_011633_f950d3` | **listed** — open, not yet claimed | Second publication of the workflow build task; `system/lifecycle` publisher, `engineering-leader` required agent type |\n| `task_20260427_010906_857c20` | **claimed** — `opencode/engineering-leader` actively working | Project handoff task; multiple task-link reports exist under this task's dir |\n\n---\n\n## How to Publish / Link / Report Safely\n\n### Publishing\n1. **Preferred**: Create a `task-request.json` with all required fields (`request_type`, `title`, `requester`, `description`, `context`, `expected_output`, `constraints`), then:\n   ```powershell\n   mycli task-hall submit-request D:\\path\\to\\task-request.json\n   ```\n   This routes through frontdesk agent, which validates completeness and generates a proper `task.md` with `## 领取门槛`. Use `--draft` if you only want a draft without listing.\n2. **Fallback** (bypass frontdesk): Direct `upload` / `upload-publish` — use only when user explicitly requests or for testing.\n\n### Linking (watched/publisher-builder mode)\n- `mycli task-hall publish-raw` or `submit-request` creates a task-link entry automatically when `publish_mode` is `watched` or `detached`.\n- Executor reports via `mycli task-hall task-link report <task-id> D:\\path\\to\\report.md`.\n- Callbacks dispatch to `publisher_agent` via `mycli task-hall dispatch-callbacks`.\n\n### Reporting (standard claim path)\n1. Write a Markdown task report (must include: `## 任务结论`, `## 完成内容`, `## 产物路径`, `## 验证结果`, `## 遇到的问题`, `## 是否需要继续`).\n2. Submit for review:\n   ```powershell\n   mycli task-hall review-submission <task-id> D:\\path\\to\\task-report.md\n   ```\n3. Do NOT submit success/fail without a proper report unless it's a trivial test.\n\n### Safety rules\n- Never publish tasks with vague titles like \"修一下 bug\" — frontdesk will reject.\n- High-risk operations (delete, push, deploy, external writes) **must** be explicitly called out in `constraints` in the request JSON.\n- Do not delete other agents' tasks.\n- `system/lifecycle` publisher tasks (like `task_20260427_011633_f950d3`) should not have callbacks dispatched to them — they have no resumable agent session (callback dispatch will `skip` with reason `system publisher has no resumable agent session`).\n- Use `claim.json` for领取 applications to avoid PowerShell parameter parsing ambiguity.\n\n</answer>\n\n<next_steps>\n\nBefore publishing any new xuanhuan/workflow task, check:\n1. Whether `task_20260427_011633_f950d3` (currently **listed**, `engineering xuanhuan workflow`) is the same scope — if so, consider claiming or collaborating rather than duplicating.\n2. The workflow project artifacts at `D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\\xuanhuan-novel-workflow\\` to understand what already exists before submitting a new task request.\n3. If your task needs a publisher-builder (watched) lifecycle, ensure `publish_mode` is set and a valid `publisher_agent` (not `system/lifecycle`) is specified so callbacks can actually be dispatched.\n\n</next_steps>\n\n</results>","metadata":{"truncated":false,"task_id":"bg_a93423f4","agent":"explore","category":"","description":"Inspect task-hall patterns","sessionId":"ses_23302e89affe6y8N0okemqUGy8"},"title":"explore - Inspect task-hall patterns","time":{"start":1777260704574,"end":1777260704588}},"id":"prt_dccfe30be001iLRUyfVHKshWk8","sessionID":"ses_233033afeffe9G1blGyyhhKVWG","messageID":"msg_dccfe20db001wHX2FnQUmqBWiE"}}
